# lib

Renders a library scope declaration as an XML context wrapper. Identical structure to app and module — the type attribute distinguishes them for the model.

# entity Input

- directive: 'lib'
- name: the library identifier (e.g. 'authHelpers', '@openhint/transpiler') — required
- body: the library's purpose, API surface, and expected usage patterns

# entity Output

```markdown
<system_context type="LIB" name="{{name}}">

{{body}}

</system_context>
```

# rule

- name is required. A lib block without a name is a PARSE_ERROR.
- The closing `</system_context>` tag must always be present on its own line with a blank line before it.
